1.1 Load packages and set plotting theme

Let’s first load the packages that we need for this chapter.

library("knitr") # for rendering the RMarkdown file
library("tidyverse") # for data wrangling

Let’s set the plotting theme.

theme_set(theme_classic()+ #set the theme 
            theme(text = element_text(size = 20))) #set the default text size

opts_chunk$set(collapse = TRUE,
               comment = "")

options(dplyr.summarise.inform = F)

1.2 Practice plot 1

Try to make the plot shown in Figure 1.1. Here are some tips:

  • For the data argument in ggplot() use: df.diamonds[1:10000, ] (this selects the first 10000 rows).
ggplot(data = diamonds[1:10000, ], 
       mapping = aes(x = cut, y = price)) +
  geom_violin() +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.1,
             position = position_jitter(width = 0.1)) +
  stat_summary(fun = "mean",
               shape = 21,
               geom = "point",
               fill = "blue",
               size = 5)
